{"lemma":"جَدَّةُ","slug":"جَدَّةُ","root":"ج.د.د","root_slug":"ج-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جَدّ","root":"جدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5156","n5164","n5165","n5166"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be new"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be serious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be earnest"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَدَّ (jadda, “to be serious, to be earnest”)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seriousness, earnestness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"diligence, assiduity, eagerness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"good luck, good fortune"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandfather"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ancestor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"glory"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Majesty"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandeur"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"excellence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ancient"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew גד (gad)."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒadd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5156","headword_ar":"جَدَّهُ","root":"jd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut it off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K.) This is the primary signification. (Mgh.) You say of a weaver,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a vawobFA","text_ar":"جَدَّ ثَوْبًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut off a piece of cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"[sufficient for a garment or the like, from the web]. (S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a Aln~axola","text_ar":"جَدَّ النَّخْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, L,) aor,"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadaAdN","text_ar":"جَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, Mgh, L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jidaAdN","text_ar":"جِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, L; [in the L, the last two forms are mentioned as inf. ns., and the former of them is mentioned as inf. n. in the Mgh; but in the K, they are only mentioned as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the S, it seems to be implied that they are simple substs., or quasiinf. ns.;])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saramahu","text_ar":"صَرَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, S, Mgh, K; *) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*~ahu","text_ar":"جَذَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaz~ahu","text_ar":"جَزَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] i.e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut off the fruit of the palm-trees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadaAdN","text_ar":"جَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~ato A^axolaAfu Aln~aAqapi","text_ar":"جُدَّتْ اَخْلَافُ النَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-camel's teats were cut off by some accident that befell her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of injury occasioned to her by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiraAr","text_ar":"صِرَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajodiydN","text_ar":"تَجْدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jd~d","text_ar":"جدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cutting off"},{"kind":"text","text":"the teat of a camel. (KL.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~a vadoyaA A^um~ika","text_ar":"جُدَّ ثَدْيَا اُمِّكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May thy mother's breasts be cut off:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a form of imprecation against a man; and implying a wish for his separation. (As, L, from a trad.) ―         -b2-  See also 5.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a","text_ar":"جَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~apN","text_ar":"جِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a garment, TA, or a thing, S, Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was new;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K;) [as though"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"newly cut off from the web;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a","text_ar":"جَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ he cut, ” or “ cut off. ” (L.) [See also 5.]       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a","text_ar":"جَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEiba","text_ar":"تَعِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) see. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadidNta","text_ar":"جَدِدٌتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [like its syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZiZota","text_ar":"حَظِظْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (L, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yajad~u","text_ar":"يَجَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~a","text_ar":"جُدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, (Mgh,) see. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"judidota","text_ar":"جُدِدْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) [aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yujad~u","text_ar":"يُجَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * Mgh, L, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, fortunate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed of good fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, L, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of good worldly fortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he advanced in the world,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in worldly circumstances;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlA^amori","text_ar":"بِالاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether good or evil; (L;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAl$~aYo'i","text_ar":"بِالشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo yujad~uwna bihimo","text_ar":"هُمْ يُجَدُّونَ بِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuHaZ~uwna bhm","text_ar":"يُحَظُّونَ بهم"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They become possessed of good fortune, and riches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiency."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Buzurj, L.) [You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a jad~uhu","text_ar":"جَدَّ جَدُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) : so in a copy of the A: probably a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a jid~uhu","text_ar":"جَدَّ جِدُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which see below: if not, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His fortune became good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his good fortune increased in goodness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, perhaps,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his dignity became great;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from what next follows].       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~","text_ar":"جَدّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY EayoniY","text_ar":"فِى عَيْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Euyuwni Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فِى عُيُونِ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suduwrihimo","text_ar":"صُدُورِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of great dignity"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation, in my eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the eyes of men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their minds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh.) It is said in a trad. of Anas,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna","text_ar":"كَانَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajulu min~aA A_i*aA qaraA^a Albaqarapa waA=la EimoraAna jad~a fiynaA","text_ar":"الرَّجُلُ مِنَّا اـِذَا قَرَاَ البَقَرَةَ وَا=لَ عِمْرَانَ جَدَّ فِينَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man of us, when he recited"},{"kind":"text","text":"the chapter of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Cow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and that of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Family of 'Imrán"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the second and third chapters of the Kur-án),]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used to be great in our eyes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a fiY AlA^amori","text_ar":"جَدَّ فِى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^amorihi","text_ar":"فِى اَمْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY kalaAmihi","text_ar":"فِى كَلَامِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a simple subst.; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~","text_ar":"اجدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was serious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in earnest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~aqa","text_ar":"حَقَّقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hazala","text_ar":"هَزَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, Msb. [In the S and A and K, the inf. n. is said to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hazolN","text_ar":"هَزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the K, it is also said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoqiyqN","text_ar":"تَحْقِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a","text_ar":"جَدَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlA^amori","text_ar":"فِى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, L, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * K, * TA,) or this is a simple subst., and the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fyh","text_ar":"فيه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~","text_ar":"اجدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (As, S, L, K;) signify also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He strove, laboured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"toiled; exerted himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his power"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"efforts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endeavours"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability; employed himself vigorously, strenuously, laboriously, diligently, studiously, sedulously, earnestly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with energy; was diligent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"studious; took pains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extraordinary pains; in the affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, L, Msb, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~afiY","text_ar":"جَدَّفِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ayori","text_ar":"السَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He strove, laboured, toiled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerted himself, in going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pace; (tropical:)  he hastened therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ayora","text_ar":"السَّيْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~","text_ar":"اجدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he hastened his course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a jid~uhu","text_ar":"جَدَّ جِدُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His labour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exertion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"energy, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extraordinary:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AizodaAda jid~uhu jid~FA","text_ar":"اِزْدَادَ جِدُّهُ جِدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his labour, &c., increased in labour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: or it may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what was not"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~","text_ar":"جِدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~","text_ar":"جِدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; wherefore, i. e. because it would be so eventually, it is here so called. (Ham p. 33. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a jad~uhu","text_ar":"جَدَّ جَدُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", above.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a bihi AlA^amoru","text_ar":"جَدَّ بِهِ الاَمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, distressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afflicted, him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) So in the saying of Aboo-Sahm,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^axaAlidu laA yaroDaY Eani AlEabodi rab~uhu\n                      \n                     \n                        A_i*aA jad~a biAl$~ayoxi AlEuquwqu AlmuSam~imu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O Khálid, his Lord will not approve of the servant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning the son,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when cutting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"biting, disobedience to a parent distresses the old man"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.)       -A6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a","text_ar":"جَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a house, or tent,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dripped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let fall drops."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","Mgh","K","L","Lh","As","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n5164","headword_ar":"جَدَّةٌ","root":"jd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end of the paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n5165","headword_ar":"جُدَّةٌ","root":"jd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a river; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~apN","text_ar":"جِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, L, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~N","text_ar":"جُدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Mgh, L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accord."},{"kind":"text","text":"to some, but correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~N","text_ar":"جُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so called because cut off from the river, or because cut by the water, in like manner as it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAHilN","text_ar":"سَاحِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is abraded by the water: (Mgh:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a river"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is near the land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~apN","text_ar":"جِدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shore"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the sea: (MF:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accord."},{"kind":"text","text":"to As,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jd~p","text_ar":"جدّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an arabicized word from the Nabathean"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kd~","text_ar":"كدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stripe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streak, that is on the back of the ass, differing from his general colour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K.) And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A streak"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, K, TA) in anything, (TA,) as in a mountain, (Fr, S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"differing in colour from the rest"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the mountain, (S,) white and black and red; (Fr, TA;) as also in the sky: (A, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"judadN","text_ar":"جُدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, S,) occurring in the Kur xxxv. 25; (S;) where some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jududN","text_ar":"جُدُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jdydp","text_ar":"جديدة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiydapN","text_ar":"جَدِيدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], which is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~apN","text_ar":"جُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadadN","text_ar":"جَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Bd.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAmapN","text_ar":"عَلَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, K,) of, or in, anything. (Th, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A beaten way, marked with lines"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut by the feet of the men and beasts that have travelled along it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Az, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"judadN","text_ar":"جُدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juduwdN","text_ar":"جُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, [app. another pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~apN","text_ar":"جُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tracks, forming lines upon the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, L.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAd~apN","text_ar":"جَادَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  [Hence, app., but accord. to the S from the same word as signifying “a streak,”]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba jud~apF mina AlA^amori","text_ar":"رَكِبَ جُدَّةً مِنَ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~apa AlA^amori","text_ar":"جُدَّةَ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He set upon a way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of performing the affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he formed an opinion respecting the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, S, A, K.) ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~apN","text_ar":"جِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["IAth","L","K","Mgh","MF","Fr","S","TA","A","Th","Az","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n5166","headword_ar":"جِدَّةٌ","root":"jd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~apN","text_ar":"جُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: ―         -b2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiydN","text_ar":"جَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rag;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece torn off from a garment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~apN","text_ar":"جُدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Ealayohi jid~apN","text_ar":"مَا عَلَيْهِ جِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~apN","text_ar":"جُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not upon him a rag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A collar upon the neck of a dog:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, L, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"judadN","text_ar":"جُدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luHFY","text_ar":"لُحًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liHoyapN","text_ar":"لِحْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or perhaps a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jidadN","text_ar":"جِدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["Th","L","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}